1
00:00:13,666 --> 00:00:17,125
[STUDENTS chattering]

2
00:00:17,208 --> 00:00:20,708
[AVRIL] I guess Kujo's
gone to the library again.

3
00:00:20,791 --> 00:00:22,791
[sighs]

4
00:00:22,875 --> 00:00:26,625
What type of girl is she,
this "Victorique"?

5
00:00:26,708 --> 00:00:30,375
[VICTORIQUE, CÉCILE grunting]

6
00:00:30,458 --> 00:00:32,875
[VICTORIQUE] Get your stupid
hands off of me, Cécile!

7
00:00:32,958 --> 00:00:33,958
Victorique!

8
00:00:34,041 --> 00:00:35,458
Don't be like this!

9
00:00:35,541 --> 00:00:36,875
One of us is going to get hurt!

10
00:00:36,958 --> 00:00:38,750
[VICTORIQUE grunts]

11
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,833
[KAZUYA]
Hey, you two. What is this?

12
00:00:40,916 --> 00:00:42,833
Kujo! Quick, get her off of me!

13
00:00:42,916 --> 00:00:44,166
[KAZUYA]
Huh?

14
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:46,000
I saw her on my way to
the classroom and thought,

15
00:00:46,083 --> 00:00:48,833
"If she's out of the library,
she can come in and say hello."

16
00:00:48,916 --> 00:00:51,208
But she's just so stubborn!

17
00:00:51,291 --> 00:00:54,083
[VICTORIQUE] ...never going,
so you might as well give up!

18
00:00:54,166 --> 00:00:55,333
What? Why not?

19
00:00:55,416 --> 00:00:58,291
I don't want to! That's
the only reason I need!

20
00:00:58,375 --> 00:01:01,583
Now, let go of me this instant!

21
00:01:04,583 --> 00:01:07,333
[CÉCILE] Well now,
it's about time you met!

22
00:01:07,416 --> 00:01:09,500
This is your fellow classmate.

23
00:01:09,583 --> 00:01:11,583
Say hello to Victorique!

24
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:45,250
[STUDENT A]
The Victorique? Really?

25
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:46,416
[STUDENT C]
From the library?

26
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:47,958
[STUDENT B]
The Gray Wolf!

27
00:02:48,041 --> 00:02:50,875
So this is...
the girl he mentioned?

28
00:02:52,125 --> 00:02:54,750
[AVRIL]
Her skin is fair and smooth.

29
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:57,125
Her cheeks are
the color of roses.

30
00:02:57,208 --> 00:03:00,083
That long,
flowing golden hair.

31
00:03:00,166 --> 00:03:02,541
Those tiny hands and feet.

32
00:03:02,625 --> 00:03:06,166
She's like a doll made by
the hand of God himself!

33
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:07,958
[CÉCILE]
Avril and everyone behind her,

34
00:03:08,041 --> 00:03:09,708
could you please
move back one seat?

35
00:03:09,791 --> 00:03:10,958
[gasps]

36
00:03:11,041 --> 00:03:12,791
Victorique, you can take
the seat next to Kujo,

37
00:03:12,875 --> 00:03:14,625
as I think it'll
help you adjust.

38
00:03:14,708 --> 00:03:16,750
Come on now. Don't be shy.

39
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:17,958
[AVRIL growls]

40
00:03:24,625 --> 00:03:26,416
Something wrong, Avril?

41
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:28,125
Just saying "good morning."

42
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:29,875
Oh, thank you. Same to you.

43
00:03:29,958 --> 00:03:31,875
[CÉCILE]
Everyone, sorry I was late,

44
00:03:31,958 --> 00:03:34,875
but a rather disturbing incident
took place this morning.

45
00:03:34,958 --> 00:03:37,791
As a result, class will be
off for the rest of the day.

46
00:03:37,875 --> 00:03:39,833
[AVRIL]
What's going on with her?

47
00:03:39,916 --> 00:03:42,958
She seems so tense.

48
00:03:43,041 --> 00:03:45,541
Hey there. Are you okay?

49
00:03:45,625 --> 00:03:47,416
You feeling sick or something?

50
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:48,916
Hey.

51
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,708
What, can you not answer
when someone talks to you?

52
00:03:51,791 --> 00:03:54,541
Or maybe Gray Wolves don't
understand human language

53
00:03:54,625 --> 00:03:56,500
like all the legends say.

54
00:03:56,583 --> 00:03:57,208
Hey.

55
00:03:57,291 --> 00:03:58,833
Little Gray Wolf.

56
00:03:58,916 --> 00:04:01,416
Or maybe you prefer
"demon girl"?

57
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:03,333
Hey, Demon Girl!

58
00:04:03,416 --> 00:04:04,541
[gasps]

59
00:04:04,625 --> 00:04:07,083
[VICTORIQUE growls]

60
00:04:07,166 --> 00:04:08,291
Impudent fool!

61
00:04:08,375 --> 00:04:10,500
Keep your hands off of me!

62
00:04:11,833 --> 00:04:14,375
Put the desk down, Victorique!

63
00:04:15,458 --> 00:04:17,416
[screams]

64
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,500
[STUDENTS scream]

65
00:04:19,583 --> 00:04:20,958
[KAZUYA gasps]

66
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:29,333
I'm glad your injury
wasn't that serious.

67
00:04:29,416 --> 00:04:31,166
[AVRIL]
Yeah, me too.

68
00:04:33,166 --> 00:04:34,333
[KAZUYA]
Hey.

69
00:04:34,416 --> 00:04:35,750
Apologize.

70
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:38,500
I will do no such
thing; thank you.

71
00:04:38,583 --> 00:04:39,875
Wait, Kujo.

72
00:04:39,958 --> 00:04:41,458
It's okay.

73
00:04:41,541 --> 00:04:43,416
You could have seriously hurt
her with that little stunt.

74
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:44,166
Say it!

75
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:45,708
Kujo!

76
00:04:45,791 --> 00:04:47,416
Listen. It's not like that--

77
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:49,375
[VICTORIQUE]
This woman is a farting newt!

78
00:04:49,458 --> 00:04:51,916
I don't talk to newts!

79
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,083
[KAZUYA]
That's it. Come here!

80
00:04:54,166 --> 00:04:55,500
Apologize to her!

81
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:56,583
Hold on!

82
00:04:56,666 --> 00:04:58,208
It's fine! Let go!

83
00:04:58,291 --> 00:05:00,541
I'm just trying to teach
farting Victorique

84
00:05:00,625 --> 00:05:02,916
that she can't treat
people this way!

85
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,875
I'm not letting go until you
apologize, understand me?

86
00:05:05,958 --> 00:05:07,333
Darn it.

87
00:05:07,416 --> 00:05:12,291
You half-baked, no talent...
mediocre excuse for a man!

88
00:05:12,375 --> 00:05:13,541
[AVRIL]
Please, stop!

89
00:05:13,625 --> 00:05:14,791
It's not like that!

90
00:05:14,875 --> 00:05:16,875
My goodness!

91
00:05:18,416 --> 00:05:20,291
[AVRIL]
A murder in the clock tower?

92
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:23,208
So another strange thing
happened yesterday.

93
00:05:23,291 --> 00:05:26,291
Do you think it's the ghost
of Leviathan, after all?

94
00:05:26,375 --> 00:05:28,083
[VICTORIQUE] Of course
the farting newt thinks

95
00:05:28,166 --> 00:05:29,583
this is the work of spirits.

96
00:05:29,666 --> 00:05:30,583
Knock it off!

97
00:05:30,666 --> 00:05:31,875
Wait, I get it now.

98
00:05:31,958 --> 00:05:33,500
That's the reason
you were so angry

99
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:36,416
when you chased me and Kujo
out of the clock tower, right?

100
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:38,291
It seemed so out of
character for you.

101
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:41,708
This isn't the first
time that someone's died.

102
00:05:41,791 --> 00:05:44,250
The tower has a history
of violent death.

103
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:45,166
That's why.

104
00:05:45,250 --> 00:05:47,583
How many times has it happened?

105
00:05:47,666 --> 00:05:49,541
This last one makes it five.

106
00:05:49,625 --> 00:05:51,583
They all happened in that room.

107
00:05:51,666 --> 00:05:55,375
Each one had a purple bruise
on their right index finger.

108
00:05:55,458 --> 00:05:57,708
Autopsies always reveal
that the cause death

109
00:05:57,791 --> 00:06:00,125
was poison injected
into that finger.

110
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:05,791
Could you tell me when the first
incident occurred, Miss Cécile?

111
00:06:05,875 --> 00:06:07,958
I believe it was the
turn of the century.

112
00:06:08,041 --> 00:06:09,250
[AVRIL] That would
put it around the time

113
00:06:09,333 --> 00:06:11,583
Leviathan left the
tower, wouldn't it?

114
00:06:11,666 --> 00:06:14,041
Were there any similarities
between the victims?

115
00:06:14,125 --> 00:06:15,583
[CÉCILE]
Uhh...

116
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:18,041
I think they were all outsiders.

117
00:06:18,125 --> 00:06:19,916
New teachers, for example,

118
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,500
or trespassing travelers,

119
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,041
friends of students, visitors...

120
00:06:23,125 --> 00:06:24,666
You get the idea.

121
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,291
[KAZUYA]
Where are you going?

122
00:06:27,375 --> 00:06:29,000
The riddle of Leviathan
can only be brought to light

123
00:06:29,083 --> 00:06:31,250
in the clock tower,
so it should be obvious

124
00:06:31,333 --> 00:06:34,125
my investigation would
have to continue there.

125
00:06:34,208 --> 00:06:37,875
My wellspring will carry me
through like it always has.

126
00:06:37,958 --> 00:06:39,833
Wait, you're not
going without me.

127
00:06:39,916 --> 00:06:43,083
[AVRIL gasps]
Kujo! I'll go, too!

128
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:51,791
[ALL gasp]

129
00:06:51,875 --> 00:06:54,291
This is rather unexpected.

130
00:06:54,375 --> 00:06:56,166
You're out of the library again.

131
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:58,541
What could it mean, I wonder?

132
00:06:58,625 --> 00:06:59,708
[VICTORIQUE]
I received a challenge

133
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:01,208
from the alchemist, Leviathan.

134
00:07:01,291 --> 00:07:03,083
I intend to accept and win.

135
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:05,000
[BLOIS]
Leviathan?

136
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:07,375
Sir? You've... got bugs.

137
00:07:07,458 --> 00:07:10,708
Ugh, I was in a hurry and
hardened it with sugar water.

138
00:07:10,791 --> 00:07:12,083
This is the end result.

139
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:13,333
So, where are you going?

140
00:07:13,416 --> 00:07:14,791
The tower is the other way.

141
00:07:14,875 --> 00:07:16,291
Investigation's over.

142
00:07:16,375 --> 00:07:17,750
I'm going back to the station.

143
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:19,791
Already? Did you find anything?

144
00:07:19,875 --> 00:07:21,333
Come, Squirrel.

145
00:07:21,416 --> 00:07:23,000
I'd like to speak with you.

146
00:07:26,166 --> 00:07:28,750
[BLOIS] Are you aware that this
school only began to accept

147
00:07:28,833 --> 00:07:31,625
transfer students like
yourself a few years ago?

148
00:07:31,708 --> 00:07:33,333
For hundreds of years before,

149
00:07:33,416 --> 00:07:35,916
foreigners were forbidden
to even enter the grounds.

150
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,916
[KAZUYA]
Huh. Why was that?

151
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,500
[BLOIS] There was a time when
this educational institution

152
00:07:40,583 --> 00:07:44,333
was actually a front
for a secret royal armory.

153
00:07:44,416 --> 00:07:47,375
Everything was kept
out of the public eye.

154
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:51,500
It's been a hiding place for
the darker parts of our history.

155
00:07:51,583 --> 00:07:53,000
We'd rather not have the people,

156
00:07:53,083 --> 00:07:55,333
or the research they did,
brought into the light.

157
00:07:55,416 --> 00:07:57,750
Leviathan being one
of the more notorious.

158
00:07:57,833 --> 00:08:00,291
And that's why you're not
investigating the case.

159
00:08:00,375 --> 00:08:03,208
It's all for the Kingdom
of Saubure's security.

160
00:08:03,291 --> 00:08:04,500
Not to mention...

161
00:08:06,375 --> 00:08:07,833
[BLOIS]
Kujo...

162
00:08:07,916 --> 00:08:10,958
If my little sister attempts
to interfere in this incident,

163
00:08:11,041 --> 00:08:12,125
I want you to stop her.

164
00:08:12,208 --> 00:08:13,458
Understand?

165
00:08:13,541 --> 00:08:16,125
We don't know what dangers
might be lurking about.

166
00:08:16,208 --> 00:08:17,166
[KAZUYA]
Danger?

167
00:08:17,250 --> 00:08:18,666
What are you saying?

168
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:22,125
I mean, powerless little
squirrels would be better off

169
00:08:22,208 --> 00:08:24,791
waiting with the Gray Wolf
until this is over.

170
00:08:24,875 --> 00:08:26,625
Now, excuse me.

171
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:29,625
Danger?

172
00:08:29,708 --> 00:08:31,333
Dark history?

173
00:08:31,416 --> 00:08:32,916
Hey, don't just stand there!

174
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,958
Let's get to the village and
bust this case wide open!

175
00:08:36,041 --> 00:08:37,500
[KAZUYA]
Sure, okay.

176
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:40,750
[AVRIL gasps]

177
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:42,875
You should come too, Victorique.

178
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:46,208
I think I'll pass.

179
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:48,000
[AVRIL gasps]

180
00:08:48,083 --> 00:08:50,625
You can go anywhere you
want with the farting newt.

181
00:08:50,708 --> 00:08:51,833
It doesn't matter to me.

182
00:08:51,916 --> 00:08:52,875
[KAZUYA hisses]

183
00:08:55,125 --> 00:08:57,750
Okay, Victorique.
Apologize to Avril.

184
00:08:57,833 --> 00:08:59,333
We've been through this.

185
00:08:59,416 --> 00:09:00,500
Victorique!

186
00:09:00,583 --> 00:09:02,541
Seriously, Kujo, it's okay!

187
00:09:02,625 --> 00:09:04,083
I'm the one who--

188
00:09:04,166 --> 00:09:06,083
Please, stay out of this, Avril.

189
00:09:06,166 --> 00:09:08,708
Now, Victorique, what is
going on with you today?

190
00:09:08,791 --> 00:09:10,458
I thought you were
nicer than this.

191
00:09:10,541 --> 00:09:13,916
I wish you'd talk to me.
You're my closest friend.

192
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:17,000
[AVRIL]
His closest friend? Her?

193
00:09:17,083 --> 00:09:19,708
Come on. Please? Let me help.

194
00:09:21,541 --> 00:09:23,166
Fine. I'm done with you then.

195
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:25,458
Let me know when you
decide to grow up.

196
00:09:26,541 --> 00:09:27,500
[AVRIL]
Uh...

197
00:09:28,833 --> 00:09:31,250
Sure you don't want to come?
You're welcome to.

198
00:09:33,208 --> 00:09:35,125
Then how about we make
a game out of it?

199
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:38,458
Whoever solves the alchemists'
riddle first is the winner!

200
00:09:38,541 --> 00:09:39,500
'Kay?

201
00:09:41,875 --> 00:09:43,041
Okay...

202
00:09:43,125 --> 00:09:45,166
I guess we'll see you later.

203
00:09:46,916 --> 00:09:48,083
[gasps]

204
00:09:57,291 --> 00:09:58,250
[yelps]

205
00:10:07,291 --> 00:10:11,250
[VICTORIQUE cries]

206
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:14,083
Kujo... You idiot.

207
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:16,250
You didn't have to get so angry.

208
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:18,166
Big dumb jerk.

209
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:25,625
[crying continues]

210
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:28,458
[gasps]

211
00:10:28,541 --> 00:10:29,750
[sobs]

212
00:10:37,125 --> 00:10:38,125
[VICTORIQUE]
That's right.

213
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:40,500
I don't have time for tears.

214
00:10:40,583 --> 00:10:42,250
Leviathan waits.

215
00:10:53,625 --> 00:10:56,250
[AVRIL]
His closest friend, huh?

216
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:57,958
Great.

217
00:10:58,041 --> 00:11:00,375
Maybe I was too harsh
on her back there.

218
00:11:04,791 --> 00:11:08,416
[gasps] Hey! There are a bunch
of names written on this one!

219
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:09,875
[KAZUYA]
Mm?

220
00:11:09,958 --> 00:11:12,166
[AVRIL] Does that mean they
were all buried together?

221
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:14,250
[OLD MAN]
Yes, five hundred years ago.

222
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:17,291
[screams]

223
00:11:17,375 --> 00:11:19,791
This tombstone marks
a Protestant grave.

224
00:11:19,875 --> 00:11:21,375
A grim reminder of the wars

225
00:11:21,458 --> 00:11:23,791
between the Protestants
and Catholics of old.

226
00:11:23,875 --> 00:11:26,500
Everyone listed here was
killed in this village.

227
00:11:26,583 --> 00:11:27,791
--[AVRIL] Hm.
--[KAZUYA] Huh.

228
00:11:27,875 --> 00:11:30,291
Some older buildings
still contain secret rooms

229
00:11:30,375 --> 00:11:32,125
that were used to hide
those being oppressed

230
00:11:32,208 --> 00:11:35,250
by the Holy Roman Empire
during the Thirty Years' war.

231
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:38,208
Now, is there something
I can help you find today?

232
00:11:38,291 --> 00:11:39,791
Actually...

233
00:11:39,875 --> 00:11:43,291
[OLD MAN] Ah, the outsiders
that were killed in the tower.

234
00:11:43,375 --> 00:11:45,125
There're no graves for them.

235
00:11:45,208 --> 00:11:48,541
Only the people of the
village are buried here.

236
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:49,833
Oh, I see.

237
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:50,541
Thanks.

238
00:11:50,625 --> 00:11:51,708
Bye, now.

239
00:11:54,208 --> 00:11:56,041
I was only a child
when it happened,

240
00:11:56,125 --> 00:11:58,291
but I remember
those days clearly.

241
00:11:59,458 --> 00:12:01,291
We should get going.

242
00:12:01,375 --> 00:12:02,791
It's scary at night.

243
00:12:02,875 --> 00:12:05,708
One time... when I
was still a boy,

244
00:12:05,791 --> 00:12:07,666
I saw an invisible spirit.

245
00:12:07,750 --> 00:12:09,875
The soul of the dead!

246
00:12:09,958 --> 00:12:11,791
[screams]

247
00:12:11,875 --> 00:12:14,791
So, how did you see it
if it was invisible?

248
00:12:14,875 --> 00:12:16,250
I'll tell you.

249
00:12:20,416 --> 00:12:22,041
[footsteps]

250
00:12:22,125 --> 00:12:23,875
[gasps]

251
00:12:23,958 --> 00:12:26,166
[OLD MAN] I definitely
heard the footsteps.

252
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:28,250
But the only sign that
anyone had been there

253
00:12:28,333 --> 00:12:30,791
where the prints on the ground--

254
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:34,291
The last marks it would
leave on the world.

255
00:12:34,375 --> 00:12:35,875
[squeals]

256
00:12:35,958 --> 00:12:37,791
[OLD MAN] Judging from
the size of the footprints,

257
00:12:37,875 --> 00:12:40,000
the spirit must have
belonged to a child.

258
00:12:40,083 --> 00:12:41,666
[KAZUYA]
And... I've lost Avril.

259
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:44,250
[SOPHIE]
♪ Doo-da-doo! Da-doo! Doo! ♪

260
00:12:44,333 --> 00:12:45,750
[KAZUYA, AVRIL gasp]

261
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:49,375
[SOPHIE] ♪ Gold that shines
bright in the sunlight! ♪

262
00:12:49,458 --> 00:12:53,333
♪ Dee doo-da-doo! Da-doo! Doo! ♪

263
00:12:53,416 --> 00:12:54,875
Oh hi, Kujo!

264
00:12:54,958 --> 00:12:56,208
What are you doing here?

265
00:12:56,291 --> 00:12:57,250
[KAZUYA]
Hi, Miss Sophie.

266
00:12:57,333 --> 00:12:58,458
Visiting someone?

267
00:12:58,541 --> 00:13:00,583
Why else would I
be in a graveyard?

268
00:13:00,666 --> 00:13:02,666
What about you?

269
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:03,916
On a date?

270
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,125
--[yelps] No, not at all!
--[AVRIL giggles]

271
00:13:06,208 --> 00:13:07,916
By the way, what was that song?

272
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,083
[SOPHIE]
Hm?

273
00:13:28,666 --> 00:13:29,708
[thud]

274
00:13:29,791 --> 00:13:36,375
[footsteps]

275
00:13:53,375 --> 00:13:54,750
And you are?

276
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:57,666
[ROSCOE] Just a traveler,
searching for something.

277
00:13:57,750 --> 00:14:00,708
[VICTORIQUE] You couldn't have
lost anything in this place.

278
00:14:00,791 --> 00:14:03,791
And yet, the beautiful
monster escaped me.

279
00:14:03,875 --> 00:14:04,916
[VICTORIQUE]
Monster?

280
00:14:07,416 --> 00:14:08,833
[VICTORIQUE]
I get it now.

281
00:14:08,916 --> 00:14:11,208
You're the companion of the
Oriental man who died here;

282
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:12,875
the red hair proves it.

283
00:14:12,958 --> 00:14:14,291
[ROSCOE]
Very good.

284
00:14:14,375 --> 00:14:16,166
Wong Kai the Illusionist.

285
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:17,708
Have you heard of him?

286
00:14:17,791 --> 00:14:19,000
Never.

287
00:14:19,083 --> 00:14:20,833
[ROSCOE]
Wong was intrigued by the film,

288
00:14:20,916 --> 00:14:23,291
"The Illusion in
the Black Tower."

289
00:14:23,375 --> 00:14:24,625
He snuck in here
to get a glimpse

290
00:14:24,708 --> 00:14:27,083
of what the film was based on.

291
00:14:27,166 --> 00:14:29,250
I take it you're an
illusionist as well?

292
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:30,416
[ROSCOE]
Yes.

293
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:32,041
How'd you know?

294
00:14:32,125 --> 00:14:34,541
Because I'm the
monster in question.

295
00:14:34,625 --> 00:14:37,375
[ROSCOE] I see.
So you know who I am then?

296
00:14:37,458 --> 00:14:38,875
Obviously.

297
00:14:38,958 --> 00:14:40,666
I also know what you're after.

298
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:43,416
And who it is you travel with.

299
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:45,625
That's very impressive work.

300
00:14:45,708 --> 00:14:48,500
There's nothing in this
world I cannot solve.

301
00:14:48,583 --> 00:14:51,375
And yet you're little more
than someone else's tool.

302
00:14:51,458 --> 00:14:52,791
[VICTORIQUE gasps]

303
00:14:52,875 --> 00:14:55,166
[ROSCOE] What could a helpless
tool raised without love

304
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:58,541
possibly understand
about the real world?

305
00:14:58,625 --> 00:15:00,958
There is nothing I do not know!

306
00:15:04,791 --> 00:15:06,166
[door opens]

307
00:15:06,250 --> 00:15:08,708
I don't think you
two should be here.

308
00:15:08,791 --> 00:15:10,166
[ROSCOE]
Who might you be?

309
00:15:10,250 --> 00:15:11,583
[CARPENTER] What's it look
like, son? I'm a carpenter.

310
00:15:11,666 --> 00:15:12,916
One of the higher-ups asked me

311
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,083
to check to see if this
place needs tearing down.

312
00:15:15,166 --> 00:15:17,208
Old buildings like
this can be dangerous.

313
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:19,708
That's why they tell people
like you to stay out.

314
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:20,875
[ROSCOE]
I see.

315
00:15:20,958 --> 00:15:22,333
We'll be careful.

316
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,333
[gasps]

317
00:15:29,416 --> 00:15:31,208
I'd like you to check
something else.

318
00:15:31,291 --> 00:15:32,250
[CARPENTER]
Hm?

319
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:35,833
We really learned a
lot from the old man.

320
00:15:35,916 --> 00:15:37,250
Yeah.

321
00:15:37,333 --> 00:15:39,083
[gasps]

322
00:15:39,166 --> 00:15:40,833
Uh, Kujo?

323
00:15:40,916 --> 00:15:42,625
Where are you going?

324
00:15:46,958 --> 00:15:51,666
[footsteps]

325
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:53,041
[KAZUYA]
Victorique!

326
00:15:53,125 --> 00:15:54,375
How are you doing?

327
00:15:55,791 --> 00:15:59,000
Hello? Hey...! Victorique?

328
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,375
You hear me, right?

329
00:16:00,458 --> 00:16:02,083
I bought you a souvenir.

330
00:16:02,166 --> 00:16:03,416
I see.

331
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:05,916
Is it another strange hat
or perhaps some candy?

332
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,750
Nope! It's a raspberry sandwich!

333
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:08,333
[snorts]

334
00:16:08,416 --> 00:16:09,375
[gasps]

335
00:16:11,666 --> 00:16:15,125
[panting]

336
00:16:15,208 --> 00:16:17,750
Oh, boy. Kujo sure can...

337
00:16:17,833 --> 00:16:18,875
--...run real fast.
--[KAZUYA] Apparently

338
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:20,500
the older buildings
have hidden rooms

339
00:16:20,583 --> 00:16:22,541
that Protestants had
used to hide out.

340
00:16:22,625 --> 00:16:24,125
I also ran into Miss Sophie

341
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:26,583
who was singing that folk song
I heard the kids singing before.

342
00:16:26,666 --> 00:16:29,041
I guess it's popular
with the locals.

343
00:16:29,125 --> 00:16:30,666
They say it's about
a group of Africans

344
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:31,791
--that lived in the village
--[BOYS singing]

345
00:16:31,875 --> 00:16:33,625
--a long time ago.
--[BOYS singing]

346
00:16:33,708 --> 00:16:35,166
[KAZUYA]
Neither Sophie or the old man

347
00:16:35,250 --> 00:16:37,500
could tell us where it came
from or what it means.

348
00:16:37,583 --> 00:16:40,791
But they were all over the
place, then just died out.

349
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:43,833
Yes, that was around
the tail end of 1873.

350
00:16:43,916 --> 00:16:45,250
I remember it well.

351
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:46,833
At the beginning
of the next year,

352
00:16:46,916 --> 00:16:49,958
the King of Saubure just up
and died without any warning.

353
00:16:50,041 --> 00:16:51,583
It was a sad time indeed.

354
00:16:51,666 --> 00:16:55,708
[KAZUYA, BOYS]
♪ Dee doo-da-doo! Da-doo! Doo! ♪

355
00:16:55,791 --> 00:16:59,791
♪ March together all for
one and one, one for all! ♪

356
00:16:59,875 --> 00:17:04,083
♪ Pretty sisters all around,
their skin as black as night. ♪

357
00:17:04,166 --> 00:17:08,250
♪ Dee doo-da-doo! Da-doo! Doo! ♪

358
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:12,541
♪ Gold that shines bright
in the sunlight. ♪

359
00:17:12,625 --> 00:17:16,708
♪ Dee doo-da-doo! Da-doo! Doo! ♪

360
00:17:16,791 --> 00:17:20,833
♪ On and on,
they rowed their oars. ♪

361
00:17:20,916 --> 00:17:26,208
♪ Trying to land
on better shores. ♪

362
00:17:26,291 --> 00:17:28,250
The gold could
refer to Leviathan!

363
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:29,750
Doesn't it make you wonder?

364
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:31,291
--Stop, Kujo!
--[gasps]

365
00:17:31,375 --> 00:17:32,333
Why? What did I do?

366
00:17:32,416 --> 00:17:34,125
I said it's a contest!

367
00:17:34,208 --> 00:17:35,666
Why are you telling
our adversary

368
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:37,625
everything we found out?

369
00:17:37,708 --> 00:17:39,333
I just thought everything
would be easier

370
00:17:39,416 --> 00:17:41,041
if we pooled our
information together.

371
00:17:41,125 --> 00:17:42,625
Isn't that a good thing?

372
00:17:42,708 --> 00:17:44,958
I thought you would have
given up by now, Newt.

373
00:17:45,041 --> 00:17:47,625
Say that again, you nasty frill!

374
00:17:47,708 --> 00:17:49,666
Did you call me a nasty frill?

375
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:50,958
What does that even mean?

376
00:17:51,041 --> 00:17:51,958
I don't know!

377
00:17:52,041 --> 00:17:53,375
It's what you are!

378
00:17:53,458 --> 00:17:54,708
Leave me alone!

379
00:17:54,791 --> 00:17:56,750
[KAZUYA sighs]

380
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:58,166
All right, then.

381
00:17:58,250 --> 00:18:01,291
Let's compare our conclusions
and get this over with.

382
00:18:01,375 --> 00:18:04,125
I think Leviathan's spirit is
wandering the clock tower

383
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:06,125
in a never-ending
state of torment.

384
00:18:06,208 --> 00:18:08,708
And he doesn't want
outsiders getting in.

385
00:18:08,791 --> 00:18:10,291
[KAZUYA]
Hold on.

386
00:18:10,375 --> 00:18:13,333
Didn't Leviathan disappear after
he was shot by poison arrows?

387
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:15,375
There was never a body.

388
00:18:15,458 --> 00:18:18,250
I think he's still alive and
killing people for some reason.

389
00:18:18,333 --> 00:18:20,125
[VICTORIQUE]
Idiots. You're both wrong.

390
00:18:20,208 --> 00:18:21,208
[BOTH gasp]

391
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:25,375
[gasps] What did you say?!

392
00:18:25,458 --> 00:18:28,750
However, your belief in spirits
is particularly stupid, Newt.

393
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:30,291
Why not come back to reality?

394
00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:32,291
So what then, you think
he's alive like Kujo,

395
00:18:32,375 --> 00:18:33,625
or is it something else?

396
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:36,666
Leviathan has been dead
for a very long time now.

397
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:39,541
He simply did a phenomenal
job of hiding that fact.

398
00:18:39,625 --> 00:18:42,833
He wasn't invincible
like some believe.

399
00:18:42,916 --> 00:18:45,250
His alchemy was nothing
but parlor tricks.

400
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:46,958
How can you say that?!

401
00:18:47,041 --> 00:18:49,458
He was an alchemist through
and through. Definitely!

402
00:18:49,541 --> 00:18:50,958
--It was all real!
--Hey, calm down.

403
00:18:51,041 --> 00:18:52,416
It's fine.

404
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:54,916
Leviathan did manage to
turn a white rose blue;

405
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,416
I'll give you that much.

406
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:58,083
Yes, he did!

407
00:18:58,166 --> 00:18:59,416
And he had an audience!

408
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:02,708
The King, the Queen,
their entire court saw him!

409
00:19:02,791 --> 00:19:04,625
Yet it was still nothing
more than a trick,

410
00:19:04,708 --> 00:19:05,875
and I'll prove it to you.

411
00:19:05,958 --> 00:19:08,291
But when I do, try not
to die of embarrassment.

412
00:19:08,375 --> 00:19:10,000
I'd hate for Kujo
to have to carry

413
00:19:10,083 --> 00:19:12,291
your flatulence-ridden
body out of the school.

414
00:19:12,375 --> 00:19:13,666
[gasps]

415
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:15,291
Now, now...

416
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:22,416
Hmph! You'll never pull it off.

417
00:19:30,875 --> 00:19:32,250
[gasps]

418
00:19:32,333 --> 00:19:34,208
No way!

419
00:19:34,291 --> 00:19:36,416
How'd you do it? Tell me!

420
00:19:41,541 --> 00:19:42,958
[KAZUYA]
Cotton?

421
00:19:43,041 --> 00:19:45,708
If you soak some in ink and
press it against a cut stem.

422
00:19:45,791 --> 00:19:48,666
you could dye a white rose
any color that you wanted.

423
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:50,208
It's a simple trick, really.

424
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:52,708
--[BOTH gasp]
--I don't believe it.

425
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:54,541
[KAZUYA]
So Leviathan really is dead?

426
00:19:54,625 --> 00:19:56,041
That's disappointing.

427
00:19:56,125 --> 00:19:57,416
I've already figured out

428
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:59,916
how he managed to pull
off most of his illusions.

429
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,125
[BOTH gasp]

430
00:20:01,208 --> 00:20:03,250
[VICTORIQUE]
But some of it still eludes me.

431
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:05,708
I'm waiting for the last
fragment to reveal itself,

432
00:20:05,791 --> 00:20:08,833
so I can reconstruct the truth
and solve this riddle.

433
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:10,708
Any thoughts on where to look?

434
00:20:21,916 --> 00:20:23,375
I think...

435
00:20:23,458 --> 00:20:26,083
Yes, it's a man
named Brian Roscoe.

436
00:20:26,166 --> 00:20:30,083
She said that ten years ago,
Brian Roscoe came back here.

437
00:20:30,166 --> 00:20:33,541
It would make sense that my baby
picture was placed here then.

438
00:20:35,125 --> 00:20:37,333
Sorry, I just remembered
something I have to do!

439
00:20:37,416 --> 00:20:39,708
[VICTORIQUE gasps]
Wait, Kujo!

440
00:20:59,458 --> 00:21:00,500
[AVRIL]
Victorique?

441
00:21:00,583 --> 00:21:01,958
[gasps]

442
00:21:02,041 --> 00:21:05,125
I'm sorry. I've been
pretty mean to you.

443
00:21:06,250 --> 00:21:08,458
You really are an
incredible person.

444
00:21:08,541 --> 00:21:10,166
The way you solve these things,

445
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:13,083
it makes... me feel like
I really am stupid.

446
00:21:13,166 --> 00:21:14,375
I don't know.

447
00:21:14,458 --> 00:21:16,458
What do you think?

448
00:21:16,541 --> 00:21:18,041
You're stupid.

449
00:21:18,125 --> 00:21:20,041
Without a doubt.

450
00:21:20,125 --> 00:21:23,791
But still... you're
free to do as you please.

451
00:21:23,875 --> 00:21:25,041
After being around you,

452
00:21:25,125 --> 00:21:28,083
I realized if Kujo keeps
spending so much time

453
00:21:28,166 --> 00:21:29,666
with a girl this brilliant,

454
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:33,000
he'll start thinking I'm stupid
and want nothing to do with me.

455
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:35,250
I guess what I'm
trying to say...

456
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:38,166
...is that I'm afraid
of losing Kujo.

457
00:21:38,250 --> 00:21:41,666
So please don't take him
away from me, Victorique!

458
00:21:41,750 --> 00:21:44,541
[wails] Sorry, this
is so embarrassing!

459
00:21:44,625 --> 00:21:46,583
Just forget I said anything!

460
00:21:48,291 --> 00:21:49,875
Huh?

461
00:21:49,958 --> 00:21:51,458
[gasps]

462
00:21:51,541 --> 00:21:52,916
Oh, thank goodness.

463
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,041
[sighs]

464
00:21:55,125 --> 00:21:57,875
[CÉCILE] Hm...
Ah, the wonders of youth.

465
00:22:03,041 --> 00:22:07,125
[LEVIATHAN] Thou who hast
found this book in the future:

466
00:22:07,208 --> 00:22:08,583
Art thou a man?

467
00:22:08,666 --> 00:22:09,541
A woman?

468
00:22:09,625 --> 00:22:10,500
An adult?

469
00:22:10,583 --> 00:22:11,916
A child?

470
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,500
[foosteps]

471
00:22:13,583 --> 00:22:14,958
[BLOIS] I mean powerless little
squirrels would be better off

472
00:22:15,041 --> 00:22:17,666
waiting with the Gray Wolf
until this is over.

473
00:22:18,708 --> 00:22:22,208
[ROSCOE]
Can I help you... little boy?

474
00:22:24,375 --> 00:22:26,958
[KAZUYA gasps]

475
00:22:27,041 --> 00:22:28,125
[LEVIATHAN]
Heed me.

476
00:22:28,208 --> 00:22:30,875
Thou must follow my
tale to completion.

477
00:22:32,291 --> 00:22:34,291
[LEVIATHAN]
If thou dost...

478
00:22:34,375 --> 00:22:36,833
...thou will know my sin...

479
00:22:36,916 --> 00:22:38,958
...and my deepest regret.

480
00:24:15,708 --> 00:24:18,083
[VICTORIQUE]
What are you waiting for?

481
00:24:18,166 --> 00:24:19,166
Take it.

482
00:24:19,250 --> 00:24:21,833
This is my answer
to your challenge.

483
00:24:21,916 --> 00:24:23,125
[KAZUYA]
Okay, give it to me!

484
00:24:23,208 --> 00:24:25,750
[VICTORIQUE]
Not you, Kujo!

